Dear {{3.properties_value.Name[].text.content}},

This refers to your request for a Personal Comprehensive Assessment and Initial Consultation (PCAIC). 

Thank you for securing the agreement and your initial payment.  
 
In order to continue the assessment and to provide you with the most effective service, we will need you to complete the following:

PROFILE QUESTIONNAIRE

{{94.text}}

We will notify you of our next steps once we receive and assess your documentation. Please reply directly to this email thread when you have completed the questionnaire. We would appreciate it if you could send your answers in a timely manner.  

On behalf of Duque Immigration Services Canada Inc., we would like to thank you again for choosing us as your Canadian immigration representative. Should you have any questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact us @ (204) 339-2522.

Furthermore, we encourage you to follow/like our Facebook page (below) as we will need to communicate with you at all times.  Please note that we have a 24 hour processing service on our Facebook page. 

We will notify you of the next steps once we received and assessed your documentation. If you have any questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact us.

IMPORTANT: Please be advised that in order to avoid miscommunication or delay in processing, please copy everyone on this email thread or click REPLY ALL on every correspondence.
 
Best Regards,

Processing Team | Duque Immigration Services Inc.

Unit 2 - 2536 Main Street, Winnipeg, Manitoba , Canada RV2 4Y2
Sunova Professional Center
Phone: +1 (204) 339-2522
Fax: +1 (204) 339-2530

WEBSITE | FACEBOOK | INSTAGRAM


1. Please be advised to avoid miscommunication or delay in processing, please copy everyone on this email thread on every correspondence.
2. Submit documents by ONE method only and in a timely manner. Sending documents through duplicate or multiple channels will result in processing delays.
3. The RCICs obligations under the Retainer/Initial Agreement are null and void if the Client knowingly provides any inaccurate, misleading or false material information. The Clients financial obligations remain.
4. Any document that is not in English or French must be accompanied by:
  • the English or French translation; and
  • an affidavit from the person who completed the translation; and
  • a certified copy of the original document.
  • Translations by family members are not acceptable.
The content of this email is confidential and intended for the recipient specified in the message only. If you are not the intended recipient, we would appreciate if you can please delete the email and notify the sender immediately.

 
  Duque Immigration Services Inc.
